cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with an algorithm for approximating the spectral norm of a matrix, which is a problem in numerical linear algebra. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves random sampling, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves information theory and signal processing techniques, which are covered in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) respectively, making them possible sub-categories.
